  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca.\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca. \u0d9a\u0dda\u0dad\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 4,708\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dc2\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Q.R. 4,708 vehicles have been tested for the code",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "QR related to National Fuel License. Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Power and Energy, said that the code had been successfully tested on 4,708 vehicles at 20 locations across the island and tests were to be conducted at another 25 locations.",
        "Due to non-delivery of orders, order delays and delivery delays, Q.R. Q.R. said that the inspection will be carried out in the next two days in 5 places where the code has not been inspected. The Minister also mentions that 3,523,729 people had registered the code as of last night."
      ],
